We came up with this word,
financial fragility,

33:42.287 --> 33:50.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
when we thought of looking at
the capacity
of families to bear a shock, to
face a shock.

33:51.029 --> 33:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Annamaria Lusardi
is an economist
at George Washington University.

33:55.834 --> 34:01.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANNAMARIA LUSARDI: And the way
we formulated
the question is, how confident
are you that

34:01.539 --> 34:09.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you could come up with $2,000 if
an unexpected
need arose within the next
month? And what

34:09.848 --> 34:17.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we found is 40 percent of
families could not
come up with $2,000 in 30 days.
So it's important

34:17.656 --> 34:21.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to recognize that, that the
financial fragility
is just so widespread.

34:21.726 --> 34:30.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EDWARD WOLFF: The main reason is
that we have
had a long period of wage
stagnation in this

34:30.168 --> 34:34.973 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country, even -- going further
back, even
to the mid-1970s.

34:35.006 --> 34:42.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, in the face of stagnating
incomes, what
did families do? Well, for a
while they did

34:42.247 --> 34:49.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
accumulate wealth, and this was
buoyed by
the housing price boom of going
forward until

34:49.921 --> 34:56.528 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
2006, and then suddenly the
housing market
collapsed, and so did net worth.

34:56.561 --> 35:02.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How much of what
you would
describe as your financial
condition is due

35:02.067 --> 35:07.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to decisions that Neal Gabler
made, and how
much of it is due to outside
circumstances

35:08.006 --> 35:09.507 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
beyond your control?

35:09.541 --> 35:14.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: That's a great
question, and
I want to take responsibility.

35:14.713 --> 35:21.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't want to put everything
off on these
larger financial forces. I chose
to become

35:21.553 --> 35:26.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a writer. This is the most
financially perilous
profession that one can possibly
imagine,

35:26.825 --> 35:28.593 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
except possibly being an actor.

35:28.626 --> 35:35.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I chose to live in New York City
because I
thought I needed to be close to
magazines

35:35.767 --> 35:42.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and publishers that I needed for
my writing
career. So I did that. And New
York is expensive.

35:42.774 --> 35:46.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I chose to have two children.
Children are
expensive.

35:46.978 --> 35:53.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I made the choice to send them
to expensive
colleges, so those were all
choices that I

35:53.218 --> 36:00.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
made that had serious financial
consequences,
but, again, those choices were
what I call

36:00.158 --> 36:01.860 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
life.

36:01.893 --> 36:05.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So many young
people today
are told, find your passion and
follow it.

36:05.230 --> 36:06.865 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It sounds like that's what you
did.

36:06.898 --> 36:13.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: That's exactly what
I did. I
followed my bliss, and I'm happy
I did. So,

36:13.138 --> 36:20.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I accept responsibility. On the
other hand,
since roughly half of Americans
are suffering

36:20.879 --> 36:27.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the same sort of financial
fragility I'm in,
we can't say that they're all
imbeciles.

36:28.019 --> 36:32.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What we have to say is that
there are forces
beyond our control.

36:32.657 --> 36:37.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let me ask you a
couple of
other questions about personal
decisions you

36:37.262 --> 36:42.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
made. You brought it up
yourself, the decision
to live here. We're in East
Hampton. People

36:42.600 --> 36:46.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
think, living in the Hamptons?
That's a really
expensive part of America.

36:46.771 --> 36:49.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: You know, when
people hear that
I live in the Hamptons, the
first thing they

36:49.474 --> 36:54.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say to me is, oh, my gosh, you
live in the
Hamptons.

36:54.212 --> 36:58.583 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
What they don't really
understand is that
there are two Hamptons. There
are the people

36:58.616 --> 37:04.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who live here full time, as I
do, who are
not wealthy, and there are the
people who

37:05.023 --> 37:06.925 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
come here during the summer who
are.

37:06.958 --> 37:14.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, yes, I do live in the
Hamptons. And when
I bought this house, I could
afford it. It

37:14.632 --> 37:20.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wasn't exorbitantly expensive. I
was able
to afford it for a very long
time.

37:20.872 --> 37:24.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is all cedar, but you can
see how many
shingles are missing here.

37:24.576 --> 37:26.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right. Right.
Right.

37:26.411 --> 37:31.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These days, though, the house
has fallen into
disrepair. It's in desperate
need of a new

37:31.182 --> 37:36.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
roof. Floorboards are rotting.
It has not
seen fresh paint in many years.

37:36.321 --> 37:38.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: If I had $100,000,
I could probably...

37:38.423 --> 37:39.357 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You could get all
this done.

37:39.390 --> 37:40.258 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: I could probably
get it done.

37:40.291 --> 37:41.759 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Yes. Yes.

37:41.793 --> 37:44.295 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Did you ever think about moving
to a less
expensive part of the country?

37:44.329 --> 37:49.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: We did. And we have
talked about
that. But here's the catch-22 of
that. If

37:49.634 --> 37:57.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we were -- once the recession
hit, the house
lost its value, as it did for
most Americans.

37:57.108 --> 38:04.582 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, now the house is
deteriorating, it's lost
its value. So if I had the
resources to fix

38:04.616 --> 38:11.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
up the house to sell it, I
wouldn't need to
sell it. That's the catch-22. I
am a financial

38:11.656 --> 38:17.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
illiterate, and financial
illiterates pay
a heavy price for their
financial illiteracy.

38:17.495 --> 38:23.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gabler is not
using the term
financial illiteracy loosely.
It's a phenomenon

38:23.668 --> 38:28.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
economists say is a key factor
in the current
fragility of the middle class.

38:28.806 --> 38:35.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANNAMARIA LUSARDI: We measure
financial literacy
by looking at basic financial
knowledge. We

38:35.413 --> 38:42.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are experiencing much more
complex financial
markets, much more complex
financial products

38:42.287 --> 38:47.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than in the past. And the
knowledge of people
has not kept up.

38:47.559 --> 38:52.830 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEAL GABLER: Half of America
will have to
compromise on their dreams.

38:52.864 --> 38:58.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's one statistic that I
cite in the piece
from a USA Today survey which I
think is fascinating.

38:58.069 --> 39:04.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that survey determined that
a middle-class
existence in America would cost
$130,000.

39:04.709 --> 39:06.411 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A year.

39:06.444 --> 39:08.179 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
NEAL GABLER: A year.

39:08.213 --> 39:17.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The median income in America is
somewhere
around $50,000. So a
middle-class existence

39:17.055 --> 39:22.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was more than two times as great
as the median
income. And what that tells you
is that the

39:22.760 --> 39:30.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
face of financial fragility is
the face of
the college-educated, as well as
those without

39:30.535 --> 39:32.303 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a high school diploma.

39:32.337 --> 39:38.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the face of white America,
as well as
the face of minority Americans,
who obviously

39:38.376 --> 39:45.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
suffer much greater. This is an
equal opportunity
situation. It affects so many of
us. It's

39:45.850 --> 39:52.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a great sadness to think that
people feel
compelled to give up their
dreams of what

39:52.390 --> 40:03.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
they thought a modest
middle-class life would
be. But they have. They have.
Even I have.

40:03.901 --> 40:15.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now: restoring
ancient cultural
treasures in earthquake-ravaged
Nepal.

40:15.947 --> 40:22.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A little more than one year ago,
a magnitude-7.8
tremor took 8,000 lives and
displaced hundreds

40:22.387 --> 40:27.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of thousands. It also destroyed
historic temples
and religious monuments that are
classified

40:27.792 --> 40:29.727 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as World Heritage Sites.

40:29.761 --> 40:34.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As part of our Culture at Risk
series, special
correspondent Fred de Sam Lazaro
reports from

40:34.399 --> 40:36.301 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Kathmandu.

40:36.334 --> 40:42.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Until now,
the major concern
in Nepal has been the
humanitarian response

40:42.507 --> 40:47.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and the slow pace of rebuilding,
as hundreds
of thousands of quake survivors
remain in

40:47.512 --> 40:50.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
flimsy, temporary shelters.

40:50.548 --> 40:57.188 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, for historians,
archaeologists and even
tourism promoters, the
earthquake did extensive

40:57.221 --> 41:04.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
damage to Nepal's historic
temples, structures
anywhere from 200 to 1,400 years
old.

41:04.462 --> 41:10.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTIAN MANHART, UNESCO: The
temples of
Nepal are absolutely unique.
They have -- they

41:10.401 --> 41:17.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are inscribed on the World
Heritage list.
So, you will find such a dense
concentration

41:17.475 --> 41:23.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of cultural heritage in almost
no country
of the world. Also, it is an
exceptional mix

41:23.848 --> 41:28.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of religions. Many temples are
Hindu and Buddhist
at the same time.

41:28.853 --> 41:33.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Hinduism has
deep -- and
intersecting -- roots here with
Buddhism,

41:33.057 --> 41:42.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
whose founder, Gautama Buddha,
was born in
what today is Nepal some 2,600
years ago.

41:42.333 --> 41:46.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rich cultural heritage is
also a living
one, says Christian Manhart of
the United

41:46.938 --> 41:49.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nations cultural organization
UNESCO.

41:49.207 --> 41:56.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTIAN MANHART: So it is not
just beautiful
monuments which are there for
tourists, but

41:56.147 --> 41:58.015 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
they are used.

41:58.049 --> 42:01.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: And that
adds more complication
to the rebuilding efforts,
already slowed

42:01.819 --> 42:06.224 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by bureaucracy and political
instability,
setting up a cultural a clash

42:06.257 --> 42:10.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR, Kathmandu
Valley Preservation
Trust: We don't have this
romanticism with

42:10.561 --> 42:16.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
historical patina. So this is,
you know, a
different way of looking at the
monument,

42:16.968 --> 42:19.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as a Westerner eye and as the
local people
here.

42:19.837 --> 42:24.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Rohit
Ranjitkar is with
a nonprofit organization called
the Kathmandu

42:24.242 --> 42:29.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Valley Preservation Trust. He
says, for most
Nepalis, these historic sites
are first and

42:29.947 --> 42:32.350 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
foremost places of active
worship.

42:32.383 --> 42:37.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: Basically, they
have the
attachment with the God and the
place with

42:37.822 --> 42:47.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the religious activities, not
with the architecture.
You know, for them, the temple
will be rebuilt

42:47.565 --> 42:50.301 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or not rebuilt. It does not make
any difference.

42:50.334 --> 42:54.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Ranjitkar's
group has
been restoring temples here for
more than

42:54.138 --> 42:59.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two decades, with funding mostly
from private
Western donors. He says the
trust's work likely

42:59.944 --> 43:02.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
helped some structures withstand
the quake.

43:02.814 --> 43:07.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Much of this complex in the
Patan neighborhood
of the capital survived, and
it's become a

43:07.218 --> 43:10.555 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shelter for antiquities salvaged
from destroyed
temples.

43:10.588 --> 43:12.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: So, these all
rescued from
the rubble.

43:12.924 --> 43:17.528 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: They are
among thousands
of icons, statues, and timbers
now housed

43:17.562 --> 43:21.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in makeshift storage until they
can be restored
to their original homes.

43:22.033 --> 43:28.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: This is one the
oldest sections
of the whole palace from 1627.

43:28.239 --> 43:34.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The temples
and monuments
are often part of royal palace
complexes.

43:34.111 --> 43:38.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's here that the delicate
balancing act
between Western or international
norms and

43:38.749 --> 43:41.486 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
local concerns comes into play.

43:41.519 --> 43:44.155 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So this is about 300 years old,
and this is...

43:44.188 --> 43:45.256 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: Last year.

43:45.289 --> 43:47.058 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Last year.

43:47.091 --> 43:51.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here, Ranjitkar explained they
decided to
repair weathered 300-year-old
architectural

43:51.496 --> 43:57.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
elements with brand-new work,
going against
the grain of many art historians
who would

43:57.034 --> 43:59.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have left the old damaged
structure as it
was.

43:59.871 --> 44:05.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: The people who
can still
do that, we need to promote
them. If we don't

44:05.376 --> 44:07.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
do this, then this skill will
also be lost.

44:07.745 --> 44:12.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He says one
priority is
to preserve the skills and
artisanship handed

44:12.583 --> 44:19.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
down the generations over
centuries, but disappearing
in a modern world economy.

44:19.457 --> 44:20.358 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Three days?

44:20.391 --> 44:21.225 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ROHIT RANJITKAR: Three days to
make this.

44:21.259 --> 44:23.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Wow.

44:23.361 --> 44:29.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The craftsmen mainly come from
lower socioeconomic
classes. Many have gone into
other work, notably

44:29.500 --> 44:34.839 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as laborers in the oil-rich Gulf
States.

44:34.872 --> 44:39.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's also a shortage of
recorded information
to guide a rebuilding that's
faithful to the

44:39.343 --> 44:45.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
original temple design. Shukra
Sagar Shrestha,
a retired archaeologist, spends
much of his

44:45.816 --> 44:54.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
time gathering old photographs,
documents,
and drawings to help the
artisans.

44:54.559 --> 44:59.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he studies the ancient
inscriptions and
intricate carvings on these
temple icons.

44:59.830 --> 45:04.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This series, for example, is a
kind of dos
and don'ts, he says, the path to
heaven or

45:04.535 --> 45:06.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hell in one's next life.

45:06.404 --> 45:11.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SHUKRA SAGAR SHRESTHA,
Archaeologist: Because
you gave your daughter to marry,
but you accepted

45:11.175 --> 45:13.077 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
money.

45:13.110 --> 45:18.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: So he has
been put into
a cauldron of boiling water
because he accepted

45:18.382 --> 45:19.917 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a dowry for his daughter?

45:19.951 --> 45:21.686 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SHUKRA SAGAR SHRESTHA: Exactly.

45:21.719 --> 45:24.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Nepal's
government says
work will begin in the next few
months on

45:24.755 --> 45:30.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rebuilding major sites that were
destroyed
with a target to finish in five
to seven years.

45:30.194 --> 45:32.296 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
UNESCO's Manhart is not sure.

45:32.330 --> 45:35.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTIAN MANHART: We were quite
optimistic.
